0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vng1705582774408_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vng1705582774408_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vng1705582774408_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ygu1665702809644\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Modifying Glyphs \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You cannot modify a glyph directly in Uniface. You must first export the image to a file and modify it using your preferred image editor, before replacing the glyph in Uniface.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__context_w3927ab1b5b1_w3928ab1b5_w3929ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__topic_d13073e1_d13074e1_d13075e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__p_d13076e1_d13077e1_d13078e1\">For example, you can create different language variations of the same glyph, or create both a color and monochrome version.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__li_d6281e1_d6282e1_d6283e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__p_d13079e1_d13080e1_d13081e1\">In the Glyph editor, select the glyph and choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Unload</span></span>. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">The glyph is copied to a bitmap file in the IDE's project directory (unless\n                  otherwise specified).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__p_d13082e1_d13083e1_d13084e1\">If the glyph contains a secondary image, the\n                  image is unloaded as two files—the primary image file with the\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">.bmp</span> file extension, and the secondary image file with the\n                     <span class=\"ph filepath\">.amp</span> file extension.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__p_d13085e1_d13086e1_d13087e1\">The original glyph remains unchanged in the\n                  Repository.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__li_d6284e1_d6285e1_d6286e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Modify the image file using your preferred image editor.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__li_d6287e1_d6288e1_d6289e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To replace a glyph, delete the original glyph object and create a new glyph object with the same name.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"ygu1665702809644__li_d6290e1_d6291e1_d6292e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To create a new variation, select the original glyph object and create a new glyph item.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831712\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831712\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Modifying Glyphs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Modifying Glyphs You cannot modify a glyph directly in Uniface. You must first export the image to a file and modify it using your preferred image editor, before replacing the glyph in Uniface. For example, you can create different language variations of the same glyph, or create both a color and monochrome version. In the Glyph editor, select the glyph and choose Edit > Unload . The glyph is copied to a bitmap file in the IDE's project directory (unless otherwise specified). If the glyph contains a secondary image, the image is unloaded as two files—the primary image file with the .bmp file extension, and the secondary image file with the .amp file extension. The original glyph remains unchanged in the Repository. Modify the image file using your preferred image editor. To replace a glyph, delete the original glyph object and create a new glyph object with the same name. To create a new variation, select the original glyph object and create a new glyph item. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}